  Annotation Scheme: Choosing the Set of Semantic Roles Because of the difficulty of defining a universal set of semantic or thematic roles covering all types of predicates, PropBank defines semantic roles on a verb-by-verb basis.
  An individual verb?s semantic arguments are numbered, beginning with zero.
  For a particular verb, Arg0 is generally the argument exhibiting features of a Pro- totypical Agent (Dowty 1991), while Arg1 is a Prototypical Patient or Theme.
